Source: libzeep
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Maarten L. Hekkelman <maarten@hekkelman.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7)
Standards-Version: 3.8.3
Section: libs
Homepage: http://www.cmbi.ru.nl/libzeep/

Package: libzeep-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libzeep2 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Library to create SOAP server software in c++ (development files)
 libzeep is a library that can be used to create a full
 SOAP server in c++. Code is generated by the compiler based
 on the signature of the methods that are exported as SOAP
 service. Makes heavy use of boost libraries.

Package: libzeep2
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description:  Library to create SOAP server software in c++
 libzeep is a library that can be used to create a full
 SOAP server in c++. Code is generated by the compiler based
 on the signature of the methods that are exported as SOAP
 service. Makes heavy use of boost libraries.
